              "fill": "#888888",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": 342,
              "content": "The Leica III was produced from 1933 to 1939 by Ernst Leitz GmbH in Wetzlar, Germany. It introduced a standardized 1/1000s top shutter speed and a separate viewfinder/rangefinder. Widely used by photojournalists in WWII. This serial suggests production circa 1936.",
